The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Nagpur, Feb. 4 (PTI): Nine farmers have committed suicide in Maharashtras Vidarbha region in the last 48 hours, an NGO said today. Three of the farmers were from Buldana district, two from Chandrapur and one each from Yavatmal, Akola, Washim and Amravati.

 With these deaths, 1,052 farmers have ended their lives since the Prime Ministers visit in July, the Vidarbha Jan Andolan Samiti said.

 New Delhi (PTI): A Delhi court has asked police to file its final investigation report by February 7 in a complaint against painter M.F. Husain (in picture) for allegedly portraying Hindu deities indecently in his works. Complainant Ram Pratap Singh had claimed there was a deliberate attempt to delay the probe. 

 London (PTI): British schoolchildren will soon have the option to learn Bengali or Urdu instead of French or German. Under a planned reform of the national curriculum, 11- to 14-year-olds required to study a foreign language will have Mandarin, Arabic, Urdu or Bengali to choose from other than European languages, The Sunday Times said, quoting a proposal by education secretary Alan Johnson.

 Lucknow: Mulayam Singh Yadav has assured some 20 protesting families from Nithari that his government would consider their demand for jobs. Many of these families, whose loved ones were allegedly killed by Moninder Singh Pandher and his servant, have not been getting jobs after the serial killings.

 Chennai: A DMK minister on Sunday launched a scathing attack on high court judges for some recent verdicts, including the repolling in the Chennai Municipal Corporation. Chief minister M. Karunanidhi praised his electricity minister Arcot N. Veerasamy for belling the cat. At a wedding, Veerasamy said: The high court should deliver judgments within the framework of the law and not try to usurp the powers of the chief minister. 

 Ujjain (PTI): Fifteen cows were found dead in mysterious circumstances near a pond, following which the VHP has called a bandh in the district on Monday. Police suspect the cows died of poisoning.




